Catalyst-Plugin-HTML-Widget-JavaScript

This is a wrapper module around Catalyst::Plugin::HTML::Widget that instead of 
creating HTML::Widget objects, creates HTML::Widget::JavaScript objects.

HTML::Widget::JavaScript is able to add some automatic JavaScript parameter
checking to your forms.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Catalyst::Plugin::HTML::Widget::JavaScript

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Catalyst-Plugin-HTML-Widget-JavaScript

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Catalyst-Plugin-HTML-Widget-JavaScript

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Catalyst-Plugin-HTML-Widget-JavaScript

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Catalyst-Plugin-HTML-Widget-JavaScript

